%h1
  Who we are

%p
  Mindapples was originally dreamt up by <a title="Andy Gibson, Sociability" href="http://sociability.org.uk/about/andy" target="_blank">Andy Gibson</a> in April 2008 during conversations around the first <a title="Social Innovation Camp" href="http://www.sicamp.org/?page_id=51" target="_blank">Social Innovation Camp</a>, and now it's being developed by a growing community of enthusiastic volunteers. Along the way we've been helped (though not financially) by <a title="The Royal Society for Arts, Manufacturing and Commerce" href="http://www.thersa.org" target="_blank">the RSA</a>, <a title="The Young Foundation" href="http://www.youngfoundation.org.uk" target="_blank">the Young Foundation</a>, <a title="Channel 4" href="http://www.channel4.com" target="_blank">Channel 4</a>, <a title="Learn new things at School of Everything" href="http://www.schoolofeverything.com" target="_blank">School of Everything</a>, <a title="Courvoisier the Future 500" href="http://www.cvtf500.com" target="_blank">Courvoisier Future 500</a> and <a title="Psychologies Magazine" href="http://www.psychologies.co.uk/" target="_blank">Psychologies Magazine</a>. We're also very grateful for the help and inspiration of <a title="Dr Liz Miller" href="http://doctorbloggs.blogspot.com" target="_blank">Dr Liz Miller</a>, <a title="Ian Gilmour, OK2B" href="http://www.ok2b.org/page2.html" target="_blank">Ian Gilmour of OK2B</a>, <a title="Simon Lawton-Smith of the Mental Health Foundation" href="http://www.mhf.org.uk" target="_blank">Simon Lawton-Smith of the Mental Health Foundation</a>, <a title="Kris Morris music" href="http://www.krismorris.com/" target="_blank">Kris Morris</a> (who did our first logo!), Charlie Davies, Tanis Taylor, Kat Pesaran and PR whirlwind <a title="Heleana Quartey, Arts PR" href="http://heleana.wordpress.com" target="_blank">Heleana Quartey</a>. There's no money or organisation behind this, just a group of collaborators peddling an interesting idea. And we're here for the love of it.

%h2
  The Mindapples Team  

%p
  The Mindapples Team currently includes official flag waver <a title="Tessy Britton is Thriving" href="http://thrivingtoo.typepad.com/" target="_blank">Tessy Britton</a>, developer <a title="Tom Ten Thij - Ruby on Rails Development" href="http://tomtenthij.co.uk/" target="_blank">Tom Ten Thij</a>, designers <a title="Ana Garcia, making the intangible tangible" href="http://www.helloanak.com/" target="_blank">Ana Garcia</a>, <a title="Sangeet Gyawali" href="http://www.sangeight.com/" target="_blank">Sangeet Gyawali</a>, <a title="Lauren Currie, Redjotter" href="http://redjotter.wordpress.com/" target="_blank">Lauren Currie</a> and <a title="Kate Andrews" href="http://kateandrews.wordpress.com/" target="_blank">Kate Andrews</a>, and research/PR gurus Neil Flintham and Jo Worsley. Plus lots of other people who are nice enough to help us out from time to time.

